min: "Casnewydd" (kas-new-with) is anything but ordinary for Newport! This unique earthhouse is Welsh-inspired, mid-century styled, and a rare find for Aquidneck Island getaways. The house sleeps up to 6 (6 adults over 12yo, max) and is outfitted for comfort and convenience, just 4 minutes to the beach and 10 mins (or less) to downtown Newport. Enjoy a super-serene location with privacy, large open living area, loads of outdoor space to enjoy, and all the necessary amenities for a perfect vacation.

min:
"If you're looking for that proverbial "All American town," and the ultimate quaint coastal New England destination, then Bristol, R.I., is the place to go.

Known as the "most patriotic town in America," Bristol abounds with American community spirit with American flags displayed throughout town and a red, white and blue median strip in its downtown. The oldest Fourth of July celebration in America, beautiful historic and incredibly well-maintained Colonial homes (one after the other on Hope Street), town buildings, and museums only augment the All-American" town look perhaps more than any other town we've visited in New England."
VisitNewEngland.com
